name: zplug
caveats:
In order to use zplug, please add the following to your .zshrc:
  export ZPLUG_HOME=$(brew --prefix)/opt/zplug
  source $ZPLUG_HOME/init.zsh

name: zsh-autosuggestions
caveats:
To activate the autosuggestions, add the following at the end of your .zshrc:

  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-autosuggestions/zsh-autosuggestions.zsh

You will also need to force reload of your .zshrc:

  source ~/.zshrc

name: zsh-completions
caveats:
To activate these completions, add the following to your .zshrc:

  if type brew &>/dev/null; then
    FPATH=$(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-completions:$FPATH

    autoload -Uz compinit
    compinit
  fi

You may also need to force rebuild `zcompdump`:

  rm -f ~/.zcompdump; compinit

Additionally, if you receive "zsh compinit: insecure directories" warnings when attempting
to load these completions, you may need to run this:

  chmod go-w '$(brew --prefix)/share'

name: zsh-git-prompt
caveats:
Make sure zsh-git-prompt is loaded from your .zshrc:
  source "$(brew --prefix)/opt/zsh-git-prompt/zshrc.sh"

name: zsh-history-substring-search
desc: Zsh port of Fish shell's history search
caveats:
To activate the history search, add the following at the end of your .zshrc:

  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-history-substring-search/zsh-history-substring-search.zsh

You will also need to force reload of your .zshrc:

  source ~/.zshrc

name: zsh-lovers
desc: Tips, tricks, and examples for zsh

name: zsh-navigation-tools
desc: Zsh curses-based tools, e.g. multi-word history searcher
caveats:
To run zsh-navigation-tools, add the following at the end of your .zshrc:
  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-navigation-tools/zsh-navigation-tools.plugin.zsh

You will also need to force reload of your .zshrc:
  source ~/.zshrc

name: zsh-syntax-highlighting
desc: Fish shell like syntax highlighting for zsh
caveats:
To activate the syntax highlighting, add the following at the end of your .zshrc:
  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-syntax-highlighting/zsh-syntax-highlighting.zsh

If you receive "highlighters directory not found" error message,
you may need to add the following to your .zshenv:
  export ZSH_HIGHLIGHT_HIGHLIGHTERS_DIR=$(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-syntax-highlighting/highlighters

name: zsh-you-should-use
desc: ZSH plugin that reminds you to use existing aliases for commands you just typed
caveats:
To activate You Should Use, add the following to your .zshrc:

  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-you-should-use/you-should-use.plugin.zsh

You will also need to force reload of your .zshrc:

  source ~/.zshrc
